HEADWORD: Wise-like
<hw>Wise"-like`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Resembling that
which is wise or sensible; judicious.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The only <qex>wise-like</qex> thing I heard anybody say.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wiseling</ent>⟦br⟧
